Vice President Kamala Harris expressed her gratitude and welcomed national leaders, labor leaders, and women leaders to her office. She acknowledged the importance of coalition building, organizing, and listening to the people. Harris also highlighted the contributions of women to America's labor movement throughout history. She discussed the challenges faced by women in the workforce, including wages, benefits, safety, and the ability to organize. The Vice President mentioned the impact of the pandemic on women leaving the workforce and the need for improvements in areas such as paid leave, sick leave, family leave, and affordable childcare. Harris thanked the leaders for their dedication and looked forward to the discussion.